       Controls the behavior of addEndCap command. Specifies a list  of  cells
       that addEndCap command uses for end-cap or triple-well cap insertion.

       Note:  The  options with *EVEN/*ODD are only for 10nm designs that need
       to fit even and odd sites. These options should not be  used  with  the
       options that do not have *EVEN/*ODD.

       For  example,  the -rightEdge option should not be used with the-right-
       EdgeEven or -rightEdgeOdd option.

       Example for 10nm design if there is EVEN/ODD sites requirement:

       setEndCapMode \

       -rightEdgeOdd <cellName> \

       -rightEdgeEven <cellName> \

       -rightBottomCornerEven <cellName> \

       -rightBottomCornerOdd <cellName> \

       -rightTopCornerEven <cellName> \

       -rightTopCornerOdd <cellName> \

       -rightBottomEdgeEven <cellName> \

       -rightBottomEdgeOdd <cellName> \

       -rightTopEdgeEven <cellName> \

       -rightTopEdgeOdd <cellName> \

       -topEdge {<ListOfCellNames>} \

       -bottomEdge {<ListOfCellNames>}

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each setEndCapMode parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man setEndCapMode.

       -antenna_tap_fill_wall_cells {listOfCellNames}
              Specifies  the  antenna  tap fill wall cell names. The wall cell
              type on boundary is different from other  locations.  When  fill
              wall  cells are also specified with the -topEdge and -bottomEdge
              options, tool uses the cells only on the boundary location.

              The following example shows that if the A and B fill wall  cells
              also present in -topEdge and -bottomEdge, then the tool knows it
              is for the boundary wall.

              setEndCapMode -antenna_tap_fill_wall_cell {AB C D}

              setEndCapMode -topEdge {A E}

              setEndCapMode -bottomEdge {B F}

              Default: ""

       -avoidTwoSitesCellAbut {true|false}
              Avoids two sites boundary cell abut to incorner cell in N10.

              Default: false

       -barrier_border_cell_bottom_y <cellNames>
              Specifies the horizontal bottom border break cell.

              Default: ""

       -barrier_border_cell_top_y <cellNames>
              Specifies the horizontal top border break cell.

              Default: ""

       -barrier_cell_x <cellNames>
              Specifies  the  list of vertical break cells which can be placed
              for barrier cells.

              Default: ""

       -barrier_cell_xy <cellNames>
              Specifies the cell to be replaced  when  vertical  &  horizontal
              break cells overlap for barrier cells.

              Default: ""

       -barrier_cell_y <cellNames>
              Specifies the list of horizontal break cells which can be placed
              for barrier cells.

              Default: ""

       -barrier_keepout_from_boundary {value_x value_y}
              Controls  the  minimum  distance  between the break cell and the
              normal endcap cell.

              * value_x is the minimum distance  between  Y-barrier  cell  and
                vertical endcap cell.

              * value_y  is  the  minimum  distance between X-barrier cell and
                horizontal endcap cell.

              The value is edge to edge spacing.

              Default: ""

       -barrier_pitch {x_pitch y_pitch}
              Specifies the Maximum Length rule of the vertical and horizontal
              layers for barrier cells.

              Default: ""

       -barrier_termination_bottom_y <cellNames>
              Specifies the list of horizontal bottom break termination  cells
              to be used for barrier cells.

              Default: ""

       -barrier_termination_top_y <cellNames>
              Specifies  the list of horizontal top break termination cells to
              be used for barrier cells.

              Default: ""

       -barrier_termination_x <cellNames>
              Specifies the list of the vertical break termination cells to be
              used for barrier cells.

              Default: ""

       -barrier_y_mode {1|2}
              Specifies the mode 1 or 2 for the barrier y cell insertion.

              Default: 2

              The image below shows mode. If mode is set as 1, the  tool  adds
              the first cell specified in -barrier_cell_y violation free.

              The  image below shows Mode2. If mode is set as 2, the first two
              cells specified in -barrier_cell_y are added by turn, and  every
              location  is  added  by  the pattern, cell + 1Cpp + cell. If you
              specify more than two cells, the other cells are ignored

       -bottomEdge <ListOfCellNames>
              Specifies the list of cells that have n-well cap on  their  bot-
              tom-edge  when  in R0 orientation. Thus, these cells are used to
              cap a top-core row, or row at the bottom of a hard macro.

       -boundary_tap
              Specifies the boundary tap and is applicable  to  getEndCapMode.
              The type is boolean.

              Default: false

       -boundary_tap_swap_flow {true|false}
              Specifies the boundary tap swap flow.

              Default: True

       -cells ListOfCellNames
              Specifies  end  cap  cell candidates for N10 that are defined in
              LEF.

       -create_rows {true|false}
              Creates rows for endtap cell techSites which do not have rows in
              the floorplan.

              Default: false

       -DoubleHeightIncornerProtrusion {true|false}
              Allows the double height in-corner cell to  protrude  into  core
              area.

              Default: false

       -enable_shrink_physical_cell_flow {true|false}
              Enables shrink left/right edge cell flow.

              Default: false

              For  more  details, see Shrink Physical Cell Insertion Flow sec-
              tion in the Innovus User Guide.

       -flipY {true|false}
              Flips the orientation of the end cap instances in Y direction if
              the site symmetry allows it.

              Default: false

       -incrementalLeftEdge <ListOfCellNames>
              Specifies the list of additional cells which should  be  treated
              as  end  cap by verifyEndCap when checking the right edge of the
              core rows or rows ending at left edge of a hard macro.

              Default:""

       -incrementalRightEdge <ListOfCellNames>
              Specifies the list of additional cells which should  be  treated
              as  end  cap by verifyEndCap  when checking the left edge of the
              core rows or rows starting at right edge of a hard macro.

              Default: ""

       -insert_nppp_wall {{Wall_Cell} {Wall_Pad}}
              Specifies the nppp wall cell and the nppp wall pad. The wall pad
              fixes the vertical CPODE max-length rule.

              Default: ""

       -leftBottomCorner <ListOfCellNames>
              Specifies a list of cells that have n-well cap on its  left-bot-
              tom  corner when in R0 orientation. These cells are added on in-
              ner corners of core, or concave corner  of  a  rectilinear  hard
              macro.

       -leftBottomCornerEven cellName
              Specifies  end  cap  with n-well at the left-bottom corner, even
              sites.

              Default: ""

       -leftBottomCornerNeighbor <cellName>
              Specifies the cell to be abutted with the left side of  leftBot-
              tomCorner in R0 orientation.

              Default: ""

       -leftBottomCornerOdd cellName
              Specifies  end  cap  with  n-well at the left-bottom corner, odd
              sites.

              Default: " "

       -leftBottomEdge <cellName>
              Specifies the one cell that has n-well cap  on  its  left-bottom
              edge when in R0 orientation. Thus, this cell, in R0 orientation,
              can  be used to cap a row ending at left-bottom convex corner of
              a hard macro, or rectilinear core; and if allowed to flip in  Y,
              it  can  be  used on MY rows that end in left-top convex corner.
              With both X and Y symmetry,  it  can  cap  all  convex  corners,
              though only R0 rows at bottom, and MY rows for top corners.

       -leftBottomEdgeEven <cellName>
              Specifies  end  cap  with  n-well  at the left-bottom edge, even
              sites.

              Default: " "

       -leftBottomEdgeNeighbor <site1_cell site2_cell...>
              Specifies the list of cells to be abutted with the right edge of
              leftBottomEdge in R0 orientation.

              Default: " "

       -leftBottomEdgeOdd <cellName>
              Specifies end cap with  n-well  at  the  left-bottom  edge,  odd
              sites.

              Default: " "

       -leftCornerBottomBorder <ListOfCellNames>
              Specifies the inner left corner bottom border cell.

              Default: " "

       -leftCornerTopBorder <ListOfCellNames>
              Specifies the inner left corner top border cell.

              Default: " "

       -leftEdge <cellName>
              Specifies the one cell that has n-well cap on its left edge when
              in  R0 orientation. Thus, this cell is used to cap right edge of
              the core rows, or rows ending at left edge of a hard macro. This
              would be same as a post-cap, in a two well process.

       -leftEdgeBottomBorder <cellName>
              Specifies end cap with n-well at the left edge, poly at the bot-
              tom boundary.

              Default: " "

       -leftEdgeEven <cellName>
              Specifies end cap with n-well at the left edge, even sites.

              Default: " "

       -leftEdgeOdd cellName
              Specifies end cap with n-well at the left edge, odd sites.

              Default: " "

       -leftEdgeTopBorder <cellName>
              Specifies end cap with n-well at the left edge, poly at the  top
              boundary.

              Default: " "

       -leftTopCorner <ListOfCellNames>
              Specifies  a  list of cells that have n-well cap on its left top
              corner when in R0 orientation. Thus, this cell is added on inner
              corners of core, or concave corner of a rectilinear hard macro.

       -leftTopCornerEven <cellName>
              Specifies end cap with  n-well  at  the  left-top  corner,  even
              sites.

              Default: " "

       -leftTopCornerNeighbor cellName
              Specifies  the cell to be abutted with the left side of leftTop-
              Corner in R0 orientation.

              Default: " "

       -leftTopCornerOdd <cellName>
              Specifies end cap with n-well at the left-top corner, odd sites.

              Default: " "

       -leftTopEdge <cellName>
              Specifies the cell that has n-well cap on its top-left edge when
              in R0 orientation. Thus, in R0 orient, it  is  the  flipped-in-Y
              version of left-bottom edge cell.

       -leftTopEdgeEven <cellName>
              Specifies end cap with n-well at the left-top edge, even sites.

              Default: " "

       -leftTopEdgeNeighbor <site1_cell site2_cell...>
              Specifies the list of cells to be abutted with the right edge of
              leftTopEdge in R0 orientation.

              Default: " "

       -leftTopEdgeOdd <cellName>
              Specifies end cap with n-well at the left-top edge, odd sites.

              Default: " "

       -min_horizontal_channel_width <channelWidth>
              If horizontal channel width is smaller than specified value, ad-
              dEndCap will cover this channel with hard blockage.

       -min_jog_height <jogHeight>
              If  jog  height  is smaller than specified value, addEndCap will
              cover this jog with hard blockage.

       -min_jog_width <jogWidth>
              If jog width is smaller than  specified  value,  addEndCap  will
              cover this jog with hard blockage.

       -min_vertical_channel_width <channelWidth>
              If  vertical  channel width is smaller than specified value, ad-
              dEndCap will cover this channel with hard blockage.

       -nppp_wall_pitch <spacingValue>
              Specifies the pitch of the nppp wall. The image below shows wall
              pitch space.

              Default: 0

              Minimum: 0

              Maximum: 2147483647

       -nppp_wall_to_FILLWALL_spacing <spacingValue>
              Constraints the spacing between nppp wall and fill wall  by  the
              specified  value. It is the edge to edge spacing as shown in the
              image below.

              Default: 0

              Minimum: 0

              Maximum: 2147483647

       -nppp_wall_to_incorner_spacing <spacingValue>
              Constraints the spacing between nppp wall and convex corner   by
              the  specified value. The following image shows constraint spac-
              ing between wall and incorner.

              Default: 0

              Minimum: 0

              Maximum: 2147483647

       -prefix <endcap_prefix>
              Adds prefix of EndCap cells.

       -reset Resets all or specified options to the default value.

              Any values that do not already match the default value  and  are
              reset will be reported.

       -rightBottomCorner <ListOfCellNames>
              Specifies a list of cells that have n-well cap on its right bot-
              tom  corner  when in R0 orientation. Thus, this cell is added on
              inner corners of core, or concave corner of a  rectilinear  hard
              macro.

       -rightBottomCornerEven <cellName>
              Specifies  end  cap with n-well at the right-bottom corner, even
              sites.

              Default: " "

       -rightBottomCornerNeighbor cellName
              The cell to be abutted with the right side of  rightBottomCorner
              in R0 orientation.

              Default: " "

       -rightBottomCornerOdd <cellName>
              Specifies  end  cap  with n-well at the right-bottom corner, odd
              sites.

              Default: " "

       -rightBottomEdge <cellName>
              Specifies the cell that has n-well cap on its right bottom  edge
              when  in  R0 orientation. Thus, these cells are the flipped-in-X
              version of leftBottomEdge cell. Usuallym one of these 2 is  suf-
              ficient for a library.

       -rightBottomEdgeEven <cellName>
              Specifies  end  cap  with  n-well at the right-bottom edge, even
              sites.

              Default: " "

       -rightBottomEdgeNeighbor <site1_cell site2_cell...>
              Specifies the list of cells to be abutted with the left edge  of
              rightBottomEdge in R0 orientation.

              Default: " "

       -rightBottomEdgeOdd <cellName>
              Specifies  end  cap  with  n-well  at the right-bottom edge, odd
              sites.

              Default: " "

       -rightCornerBottomBorder <ListOfCellNames>
              Specifies the inner right corner bottom border cell.

              Default: " "

       -rightCornerTopBorder <ListOfCellNames>
              Specifies the inner right corner bottom border cell.

              Default: " "

       -rightEdge <cellName>
              Specifies the cell that has n-well cap on its right edge when in
              R0 orientation. Thus, these cells are used to cap the left  edge
              of  the  core-rows  in  R0. In 2 well process, this would be the
              pre-cap cell.

       -rightEdgeBottomBorder <cellName>
              Specifies end cap with n-well at the right  edge,  poly  at  the
              bottom boundary.

              Default: " "

       -rightEdgeEven <cellName>
              Specifies end cap with n-well at the right edge, even sites.

              Default: " "

       -rightEdgeOdd <cellName>
              Specifies end cap with n-well at the right edge, odd sites.

              Default: " "

       -rightEdgeTopBorder <cellName>
              Specifies end cap with n-well at the right edge, poly at the top
              boundary.

              Default: " "

       -rightTopCorner <ListOfCellNames>
              Specifies  a  list  of cells that have n-well cap on their right
              top corner when in R0 orientation. Thus, this cell,  in  R0,  is
              added  on right corner of core, or concave corner of a rectilin-
              ear hard macro.

       -rightTopCornerEven <cellName>
              Specifies end cap with n-well  at  the  right-top  corner,  even
              sites.

              Default: " "

       -rightTopCornerNeighbor <cellName>
              Specifies  the  cell to be abutted with the right side of right-
              TopCorner in R0 orientation.

              Default: " "

       -rightTopCornerOdd <cellName>
              Specifies end cap with  n-well  at  the  right-top  corner,  odd
              sites.

              Default: " "

       -rightTopEdge <cellName>
              Specifies  the  cell  that  has n-well cap on its right top edge
              when in R0 orientation. Thus, this cell is the R180  version  of
              leftBottomEdge.

       -rightTopEdgeEven <cellName>
              Specifies end cap with n-well at the right-top edge, even sites.

              Default: " "

       -rightTopEdgeNeighbor <site1_cell site2_cell...>
              Specifies  the list of cells to be abutted with the left edge of
              rightTopEdge in R0 orientation.

              Default: " "

       -rightTopEdgeOdd <cellName>
              Specifies end cap with n-well at the right-top edge, odd sites.

              Default: " "

       -topBottomEdge <ListOfCellNames>
              Specifies the cell that has an n-well cap on  its  top  edge  as
              well as bottom edge when in R0 orientation.

       -topEdge <ListOfCellNames>
              Specifies  the  list  of cells that have n-well cap on their top
              edge when in R0 orientation. Thus, these cells are used  to  cap
              the bottom-core row, or row at top of a hard macro.

       -useEvenOddSite {none|even|odd}
              Specifies to use even or odd poly sites.

              * none: EVEN/ODD cells are not considered even if they are spec-
                ified

              * even: Need to specify EVEN boundary cell, suc as -leftEdgeEven

              * odd: Need to specify ODD boundary cell, such as -leftEdgeOdd

              Default: none

       -wall_keepout_from_vertical_boundary <macro>
              Specifies  the  wall  keep-out  spacing from left/right boundary
              cell.

              Default: 0

              Minimum: 0

              Maximum: 2147483647

       -wall_offset <macro>
              Specifies the x coordinate of the first wall column.

              Default: 0

              Minimum: 0

              Maximum: 2147483647

       -wall_pitch <macro>
              Specifies the wall pitch.

              Default: 0

              Minimum: 0

              Maximum: 2147483647

       -wall_shift_step <macro>
              Controls   the   fillwall   shift   step.   When   you   specify
              -wall_shift_step,  the  wall  step  defines increment for moving
              fillwall to the left side of the  original  location.   If  wall
              must be moved, the distance of the movement should be an integer
              multiple  of  the "step". The next wall keeps the fillwall pitch
              with the moved fillwall.

              If there is a conflict between fillwalls and  macro  edges  when
              the fillwall is shifted with the defined step:

              * The  original location and the shifted step location, based on
                original location, will be the first selected to put the fill-
                wall.

              * If the first selected fillwall conflicts with the macro edges,
                fillwall will fall back to the old behavior (ignore "step") to
                find an available location.

              Each of the next wall will first select and satisfy the  max  OD
              length rule.

              Default: 0

              Minimum: 0

              Maximum: 2147483647

       -wall_to_convex_corner_spacing <macro>
              Constraints the spacing between wall and convex corner.

              Default: 0

              Minimum: 0

              Maximum: 2147483647

Example
              * The  following command controls that the cell ABC being placed
                at the end of each row and cell XYZ being placed at  beginning
                of each row by addEndCap command:

       setEndCapMode -leftEdge ABC -rightEdge XYZ

              * An  example  of a library with 4 types of cells, RightEdge RE,
                TopEdge TE, LeftTopEdge LTE, and LeftTopCorner LTC, would have
                the following placement of end caps:

              *

                * Pre-caps for start of rows would be cap_RE in R0 (N) and  MX
                  (FS) orient.

              *

                * Post-caps  for  end  of  rows would be cap_RE in MY (FN) and
                  R180 (S) orient.

              *

                * Caps for bottom of core, and in core-row  on  top  of  macro
                  blocks  would  be  cap_TE in R0 (N) orient (i.e. core has to
                  start from R0 row; else the bottom FS row would be wasted).

              *

                * Caps for top of core, and at bottom of macro blocks would be
                  cap_TE in MX (FS) orient (that is, if block gets placed on a
                  FS row, and row below it is N row, then the N row has to  be
                  blocked so caps can be placed below it on FS orient row).

              *

                * A cap_LTE cell can be used at 4 corners in R0 (left-bottom),
                  MY  (right-bottom), R180 (right-top), and MX (left-top) ori-
                  ent.

              *

                * Similarly, a cap_LTC cell is used for inner edges of a  rec-
                  tilinear  block  macro  in its 4 orients, just as the corner
                  cell.

       All the cells need to have SYMMETRY X Y defined in LEF.

              * The image below is an Illustration of LEFTEDGETOPBORDER, LEFT-
                EDGEBOTTOMBORDER, RIGHTEDGETOPBORDER and RIGHTEDGEBOTTOMBORDER

